text.section:
A special limited charity fundraising event may be held:
On or in the premises of a licensed charitable organization;
In a licensed charitable gaming facility, subject to restrictions contained in KRS 238.555(7); or
At an unlicensed facility under the following conditions:
An unlicensed facility shall host no more than one (1) special limited charity fundraising event per year;
The facility shall be closed to the general public during the conduct of a special limited charity fundraising event or the event shall be held in a separate room or area not accessible to the general public;
Equipment used in the conduct of a special limited charity fundraising event shall be removed from the premises within two (2) working days after the event; and
The unlicensed facility shall be subject to requirements stipulated in KRS 238.555(3).
